The paper deals with the combinatorial properties of words and introduces a new tool to investigate them. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) categories. The paper also discusses the approximation algorithms for finding the smallest string attractor, which falls under the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) category. Additionally, the paper explores the notion of string attractors for different families of finite words, which suggests that it may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Information Theory (cs.IT) categories.
